          The poultry grandparent and parent project will be located in Toushka, in the south of Egypt, on a total land area of 4,800 acres (undeveloped desert land).  The Wadi food complex in KM54 is on land already owned and developed by Wadi, and where Wadis current grandparent farms, olive orchards and olive oil press are located.
